---

# 2. Project Overview

For this project, I created a static interactive food website called **Midnight Cravings**. The purpose of the website is to recommend late-night food cravings such as pizza, ramen, and chocolate dessert. The website includes interactive JavaScript features such as:

* Random craving generator
* Mood-based food recommendations
* Clickable food cards
* Dark/light mode
* “Add to Cravings” popup interaction

The project was developed to practice website hosting, DNS configuration, GitHub Pages deployment, custom domains, and HTTPS setup.

---

# 3. Tools and Technologies Used

The following tools and technologies were used during the project:

* HTML
* CSS
* JavaScript
* Visual Studio Code
* GitHub
* GitHub Desktop
* GitHub Pages
* Cloudflare Registrar
* Cloudflare DNS

No database was used because the website is fully static.

---

# 4. Website Development Process

First, I created the project structure inside Visual Studio Code. The project included the following folders and files:

```text
index.html
css/style.css
js/script.js
images/
```

The **HTML** file was used to create the website structure, including the navigation bar, hero section, food cards, mood section, about section, and footer.

The **CSS** file was used to design the website layout, colors, responsive design, animations, buttons, and food cards.

The **JavaScript** file was used to add interaction and functionality such as:

* Theme toggle (dark/light mode)
* Random craving generator
* Mood recommendation buttons
* Clickable food cards
* Popup messages

After developing the website locally, I uploaded the project to GitHub using GitHub Desktop.

---

# 5. GitHub Pages Setup

After creating the GitHub repository, I enabled GitHub Pages from the repository settings.

The configuration used was:

```text
Source: Deploy from a branch
Branch: main
Folder: /root
```

GitHub Pages then automatically published the website using the default GitHub Pages domain.

---

# 6. Custom Domain Setup

To make the website look more professional, I purchased the custom domain:

```text
cithost.com
```

using Cloudflare Registrar.

After purchasing the domain, I configured the DNS records in Cloudflare DNS so the domain would point to my GitHub Pages website.

---

# 7. DNS Configuration

The following DNS records were added in Cloudflare DNS:

```text
Type: CNAME
Name: @
Target: merkamemaj.github.io
Proxy status: DNS only
```

```text
Type: CNAME
Name: www
Target: merkamemaj.github.io
Proxy status: DNS only
```

These records connected the custom domain to GitHub Pages.

