# 10. Challenges Faced

One challenge was connecting the local project files to GitHub correctly. Initially, I had issues pushing updates and syncing the repository. I solved this by using GitHub Desktop, which simplified committing and pushing files.

Another challenge was DNS propagation and HTTPS activation. At first, GitHub Pages displayed a message saying the HTTPS certificate had not yet been issued. This problem was resolved by waiting for DNS propagation and refreshing GitHub Pages settings later.

I also experienced issues with image paths and CSS file names. Some images did not load correctly because the file names in HTML did not exactly match the actual image names inside the images folder. I fixed this by correcting the image paths and ensuring the filenames matched exactly.

---

# 11. Conclusion

This project helped me understand how a real website is developed, hosted, and connected to a custom domain. I learned how GitHub Pages works, how DNS records connect domains to websites, and how HTTPS secures website traffic.

The final website is publicly accessible using a custom domain and HTTPS encryption, making it function similarly to a real deployed website.
